The article is a speech given by the First Lady, Jill Biden, at the East Room of the White House. She begins by expressing gratitude for Italy's support in Ukraine and discusses her own Italian heritage. She reminisces about her grandparents and the values they brought with them to America. She also acknowledges the struggles faced by Italian immigrants and the discrimination they experienced. She praises Speaker Pelosi and other elected officials for embodying these values and working towards a better future. She highlights President Biden's efforts to build a strong economy and create opportunities for all. She emphasizes the enduring determination and legacy of immigrants, inviting the audience to feel at home in the White House. The speech concludes with an introduction of Cecilia Sordoni and a toast to shaping the country and passing on ancestral dreams and values.